passages.text: Privia Health Group, Inc. PRVA | \(\) 21.85\(Outperform | Target Price / Base Case:\) \ \(200\) Commentary

What happened? CMS recently released MSSP performance data for Performance Year (PY) 2024, highlighting that the overall program generated savings of \(>\) 2.5 Bn (vs. \(>\) 2.1 Bn in PY23). This year Privia's nine plans saw stronger yoy savings as well as a higher level of savings vs. the overall MSSP average.

Our Take: Once again, PRVA delivered strong MSSP performance, at almost double the savings rate vs. the MSSP average in its nine plans. As with last year, the most established plans delivered the highest levels of savings. Overall, PRVA achieved \(\) 233.1\(MM in net savings, up\) \sim 32\% \(vs. the\) \ \(176.6\) MM of savings for PY23. After CMS takes its share, PRVA could see \(\sim\) 155 MM in MSSP revenue.

In conjunction with the reported results, PRVA also raised its full year EBITDA guidance to \(\) 113- 116\(MM (vs.\) \ \(109- 111\) MM prior and St et of \(\) 112\(MM), and expects to report additional guidance updates on its 3Q call in November. Overall, we see today's results as a positive outcome vs. expectations where there were some worries that PRVA would not be able to drive as much yoy improvement as MSSP results show.
